{
  "text": "To probe the partitioning of the PAHs, DRMs were prepared from multilamellar vesicles as previously described [CITATION_1] , with slight modifications. Briefly, multilamellar vesicles were formed by thin film hydration. The appropriate amount of lipids, dissolved in chloroform/methanol 9:1, were mixed and solvents were evaporated by rotary evaporation. Next, the lipid film was hydrated in 10 mM Tris-HCl, 150 mM NaCl, pH 7.4 by repeated vortexing at 60 \u00b0C ; the final lipid concentration was made 1 mM. To isolate DRMs, ice cold Triton X-100 was added to chilled MLVs in a 1:1 mol Triton X-100 to lipid ratio. These conditions were chosen to observe similar perylene partitioning in the vesicles with DRMs as in the GUVs with L d and L o phases (see Figure 5 ). After 30 minutes of incubation on ice, the DRMs were obtained by ultracentrifugation at 227,000 g for 1 h at 4 \u00b0C . The supernatant was removed and the pellet resuspended in the same volume of Tris/NaCl buffer. Fluorescence of the pellet and the supernatant was measured on a fluorimeter (Jasco FP-8300). ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "29618253"
